values: So totally loving plymouth so far. Kinda sucks we have to start work soon, but it will be chill. Love living with jen, and no matter what anyone says..Im not annoyed by Jen and Chris, and people know me well enough to know that I would say something and be honest if I was. Anyway, everything so exciting, all good. WOOHOO!!

Ok, so back here at plymouth, I was unpacked and set up in two hours. Thank goodness, because it was truly the most dreadful drive to plymouth ever!! Anyway back at plymouth....I don't want to go to school though...that sucks. Anyway...I am finally online thanks to Christian. OK, talk to you all later.

Ok, so tomorrow is Plymouth, I am very excited. While I won't forget about my Camden Summer Counselor Buds--Cameron, Rachele, Brandon and Will. I will be happy to be with my plymouth family again..literally, mommy, daddy, brother, and uncle, also known as Jen, Chris, Dan and Derrick. HAHA. I probably won't be sleeping too much tonight, a little too hyper, and tomorrow I get to get my glamour shots pictures and a STARBUCKS frappaccino, I will be totally hyped for the day after that thing. Apparently we are going to have a back to school celebration watching the VMAs, that will be awesome. Then Monday..haha time to get ready for school, buying books aka going broke, and then maybe walmart?? Getting to plymouth isn't complete without going to the town hangout of walmart. Anyway, I will see you all tomorrow.

Well...I parallel parked perfectly...but I didn't pass. :-( You know what I did wrong? One thing--I didn't look over my left shoulder to get out of the parking space. Can you believe that? How anal can they be, I drove around for 20 minutes perfectly, and I don't look over my shoulder once and they don't give it to me!! That's why they put mirrors on the car!! I looked in all the mirrors, no one was there.. and no one was coming! How retarded can they be? So I have a car, but no license. They are really anal about that stuff in maine. I know people who have had to take it 3 or 4 more times before they got their license. They are really pathetic about it. On the up side according to my dad..I don't have to pay for insurance since I don't have my license. Therefore I have an extra hundred something dollars, which is always nice, my dad said I deserve to treat myself to something nice, like dance clothes/accessories or something. So, I'm pretty mad about that, because at the age of twenty I would like to be able to transport myself places. Derrick will you take me places--like walmart?? Anyway, back at plymouth soon. Room decorating, and arranging, and a nice full dance studio and pianos!

Ok, so school is this sunday...tomorrow is my driving test for the second time. I failed the first time because I hit the curb trying to parallel park. Sooo the only thing keeping from my license is parallel parking, how annoying is that? I will never do this again, but in order to have my car to be able to go some places, like walmart, when at plymouth, i need to do it. So i have been practicing my parallel parking for the past week, and in about 14 hours I have to take my test. I parallel parked perfectly the past two days, so I think I'm ready, but I'm not getting overconfident, because these driving people are pretty anal about stuff. Anyway, so plymouth is this sunday, I'm pretty excited about it, but I have to make sure that I get to say goodbye to my homeboy counselors and everyone. Anyway, PSU soon. Ciao.

Clay Clay Clay!!!! OMG I LOVE HIM SOOOO MUCH, I saw him live and still cannot believe it or get enough of him. I cried at the concert because he is soo wonderful and inspirational. I love him so much, ok tomorrow is the last day of camp, will definitely miss my buds, but all good, I love them. Anyway..woohoo..I love clay.

Summer is a blast, camp is fabulous, as are my group of counselors who are all now by best friends. We are literally FRIENDS--Ross, Rachel, Chandler, Phoebe, Monica and Joey. Yeah, we really are, it's funny. Anyway, yeah, not really missing plymouth at all, just the ding of the clock tower. Hopefully going on a trip with my buds after camp ends, so that will be a blast too.

Quick question to my live journal buds, how much older is too old to date someone? As in--me being the older one. That is my question, yeah I have a smallish crush on a fellow counselor, who happens to be a little bit younger than me. We are "Bus buddies" we sit together on the bus everyday--LOL. Anyway let me know what you all think. Thanks, mwah and hugs to all of you, I miss you. Love mandy.
